    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1991 BMW M3 is a museum-grade example featuring the legendary S14 2.3L inline-four, breathing through factory individual throttle bodies for instantaneous throttle response. The Getrag 265 dogleg 5-speed manual transmission shifts with surgical precision, delivering power to the rear wheels via a 25% locking limited-slip differential. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, retaining its original MacPherson front struts and semi-trailing arm rear setup with no signs of fatigue or oxidation. Meticulously preserved, this unit boasts matching numbers, original VIN-tagged panels, and a flawless interior. A true homologation special with zero mechanical compromise or parasitic loss.",
